articles.title: Incomplete neurovascular imaging work-ups to blame for subsequent stroke in patients with TIA - Health Imaging
articles.description: Up to 37% of patients presenting with transient ischemic attack do not receive a full neurovascular imaging work-up, according to new data published in the American Journal of Roentgenology.
